                <head>No. 64.</head>
                <dateline>[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1798-12-31T23:59:59-04:56"
                        notBefore="1798-01-01T00:00:00-04:56" when="1798">undated</date>]</dateline>
                <p rend="italic">
                    <hi rend="italic">Extract of Voyage of Captain Vancouver.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Soundings in some places only could be gained close to the shore; and in the
                    middle no bottom had anywhere been found with 100 fathoms of line, although the
                    shores were in general low, and not half a league asunder.—(Vol. 1, p. 240.)<seg
                        type="margin">No soundings appear on Vancouver’s map where the water is of
                        great depth.</seg>
                </p>
                <p>As we stood to the westward, our depth soon increased to fifteen fathoms, after
                    which we gained no bottom until we reached the western shore of the gulf.—(Vol.
                    1, p. 299.)</p>
            </div>
